amining method coverage**\\n\\nI'm reviewing the method call for `getEventFactoryPid`, ensuring all call sites are covered. It seems that all the remaining lines in the constructor will be covered if it runs properly, and that registration and event handling are fully addressed. The `findConfiguration` method is covered by the `CM_UPDATED` event, which is great. \\n\\nI should also consider how line 127 uses `proxy.newProxyInstance` with `listenerClass.getClassLoader`. If we’re dealing with Native Image, the proxy config will be generated by the agent. Additionally, I might want to include `ConfigurationEvent.CM_DELETED` along with methods like `getEventPid` and `getType` for completeness.\\n\\n**Considering git changes**\\n\\nI’m thinking about an existing placeholder that seems unrelated. Maybe I could remove it or make it a no-op, but I wonder if that would conflict with the guideline about keeping active class coverage in its own file. I need to check if my tests are in the correct file. To finalize my plan, it could be helpful to run `git diff` to see any changes, particularly excluding untracked files. I'll also use `git status` to double-check.\", \"thinkingSignature\": \"{\\\"id\\\":\\\"rs_03ad01c0eee629e20169f62716455c819fb8f9661c976abd63\\\",\\\"type\\\":\\\"reasoning\\\",\\\"encrypted_content\\\":\\\"gAAAAABp9icm15fKtF3GqJhyccnbRQcqYyvJDmHQz3PXovsnsuWQVoi9FPrDX26p_GI32dxB6vJOFs1Sx9xLMmC5E-TGJbLP-fF_7PqRLhHQTYn1eiSaKEklAqYWE8XVDODvx3U8lZbne2sWs9b2jCB1Xv4fCZNAwcsFDJN2vKTzKAravWNLNa2m-09GvMUXMTNOYwZCvXupgbedhsMas762EEEiRbsHEvNy8F5-Y-t6UFOpdrICK6L6eZCC4BQ2QUTWz0zWAaaOC7hxhavzbexdoSBL_1r_XrYCKQsa18sIIPRavXgQf7qx9ceHkblVv8kB1Dc7QtQUVa4sQW9-Q9jgBMdFb38z4Pxg_wKmR7gAWM6iKWC54HP46xauAMdzQH3swho-2guVlcn4vbBDDSKC3iBiv_PYXFfo4Whl3vKMQaGxraDWWbTlq7QBvO6-4sGWju2PhW9F8lc9v8Ijx-ie0Lw4nudTgiN-q_bi-rSMNrtgJruu8e-gb8ceZaHScb79DKb375BRe7AK4H0HcHZVraXtb-3TyXgNhKQfIZFhU3yBpd82ptsXhOKHyzHDErmyX_bZaEmos5-ndCwMfFDzSTEwyQxdClfdTvBUtyxWXiA3Hv1oNK2mpA63j-dGvyGenor6KtA0PeQ570K0IFuaXY_